content.problemStatement:
In this lesson, we'll learn how to use `for` loops to iterate over strings in Java, allowing us to process each character individually. Strings in Java are sequences of characters, accessible using their index, starting from `0`.

---

**Example:**
```java
class Seedit {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Define a string variable to hold the text we want to iterate over
        String text = "Java 2025";

        // Use a for loop to iterate through each character in the string
        // The loop runs from index 0 to the last index (text.length() - 1)
        for (int i = 0; i < text.length(); i++) {
            // Extract the character at the current index
            char character = text.charAt(i);

            // Print the character along with its index
            System.out.println("Character at index " + i + ": " + character);
        }
    }
}

```

**Expected Output:**
```default
Character at index 0: J
Character at index 1: a
Character at index 2: v
Character at index 3: a
Character at index 4:
Character at index 5: 2
Character at index 6: 0
Character at index 7: 2
Character at index 8: 5
```

